DOCUMENT();       

loadMacros("PG.pl",
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl",
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl"
           );
       
TEXT(beginproblem()); # standard preamble to each problem.


$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$x1 = random(0.1,0.5,0.1);
$x2 = random(0.6,0.9,0.1);
$y1 = $x2;
$y2 = random(-0.9,-0.2,0.1);
$m = ($y1-$y2)/($x1-$x2);
$b = $y1 - $m*$x1;
$dy = $y1-$y2;
$dx = $x1-$x2;
$ans = "$m x + $b";


BEGIN_TEXT
Question 22:
$BR $SPACE $BR
Find an equation for the linear function which has $BITALIC f( $x1 ) = $y1 $EITALIC and $BITALIC f( $x2 ) = $y2 ${EITALIC}.   
$BR $SPACE $BR
\( f(x) = \ \) \{ ans_rule(20) \}
END_TEXT

ANS(fun_cmp($ans,vars=>'x'));

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR
$BBOLD SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR
We have $BITALIC f( $x1 ) = $y1 $EITALIC and $BITALIC f( $x2 ) = $y2 ${EITALIC}.  This gives $BITALIC f(x) = mx + b $EITALIC where
$BR
\[ m = \frac{$y1 - $y2}{$x1-$x2} = \frac{$dy}{$dx} = $m \]
$BR
Solving for $BITALIC b $EITALIC we have $SPACE \( f( $x1 ) = b + ($m)($x1) \) $SPACE and therefore
$BR
\[ b = f( $x1 ) - ($m)($x1) = $y1 - $m($x1)=$b \]
$BR
So \( f(x) = $m x + $b \)
$BR
END_SOLUTION
ENDDOCUMENT();   # This should be the last executable line in the problem.